                            <h2 style="color: #fcc454;">Keto Diet</h2>
                            <p>
                                The Keto Diet is a low-carbohydrate, high-fat diet that is designed to put the body into a metabolic state called ketosis. By restricting carbohydrate intake and increasing fat intake, the body starts to burn fat for energy instead of glucose from carbohydrates. This can lead to weight loss and other health benefits.

                                The Keto Diet typically involves consuming less than 100 grams of carbohydrates per day and getting the majority of calories from fat sources such as meat, dairy products, oils, and nuts. Protein intake is moderate and should be sufficient to maintain muscle mass.

                                While the Keto Diet has been shown to be effective for weight loss and improving certain health markers, it may not be suitable for everyone. People with certain medical conditions or on certain medications may need to avoid this diet, and it is always important to consult with a healthcare professional before starting any new diet or exercise program.
